cs.CV, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for bone surface delineation in ultrasound images, which involves using image descriptors and ultrasound propagation constraints. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques for learning the local likelihood of soft tissue and acoustic-shadow regions suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the use of factor graphs and edge potentials suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
